Write a program to:

Create a file name Lab_7.txt if it does not exist.
Create the following String:  The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog
Create an array from the string so each word is a separate array element
Write the words from the array into the file using text I/O.
Read the data back from the file and place into an array.
Sort the array and display the words on the screen in increasing order.

What do we need?

-PrintWriter
-Scanner
-An array; perhaps an Arrays class
